The paper discusses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and its applications in digital media research, which are typically covered in the arXiv categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper specifically focuses on the symbolic representation of CNNs using Symbolic Tensor Neural Networks (STNN) and its applications in digital media, which is a topic that falls under these categories. Therefore, these categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
